<HEADLINE>
FT  04 SEP 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Fast printers to cope with the
load
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JENNIE LYNCH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Printing lengthy reports or documents, so often a slow and tedious process,
could be quicker and less fiddly using the latest laser printers from
Compaq.
The Pagemaq 15 and Pagemaq 20 are capable of printing 15 and 20 pages per
minute respectively. Both have a paper capacity of 1,500 sheets, thus
minimising trips to the printer to reload.
The new printers connect directly to Novell and Apple networks and can cope
with input from five sources simultaneously. The incorporation of Adobe
PostScript and PCL5 page description languages means only one printer is
required to satisfy the needs of two different software systems.
The Pagemaq 20 is aimed at networks of up to 20 users each; it retails at
Pounds 3,295. The Pagemaq 15 is slightly cheaper at Pounds 2,625 and may be
better suited to smaller concerns. Compaq Computer: UK, 081 332 3354.
</TEXT>
