FT  04 SEP 92 / The Lex Column: Dividends
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
No less than 12 UK companies with a stock market capitalisation of more than
Pounds 100m - including five Footsie constituents - reported interim figures
yesterday. Not one of them cut their dividend. The average increase in their
payouts, indeed, was broadly in line with inflation at 3.8 per cent. On the
view that dividends are one expression of a company's confidence over the
medium term, the trend must be mildly encouraging. It is worth pointing out,
however, that while yesterday's sample reflected a wide spectrum of
businesses, the only representative from the stricken building sector was a
small housebuilder of proven quality.
