<HEADLINE>
FT  04 SEP 92 / Car sales figures expected to be low
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FIGURES for last month's sales of new cars, to be published today, are
expected to show that registrations were virtually unchanged from a year ago
at about 370,000, Kevin Done writes.
The result is a serious setback for the motor industry, which had hoped that
August would mark the beginning of the long-awaited recovery in demand for
new cars.
Most leading carmakers had earlier forecast sales in August of about 400,000
and the industry now faces a serious problem of excess stocks.
Mr Ian McAllister, chairman of Ford of Britain, the leader of the UK new-car
market, said that sales for the full year were now forecast to total no more
than 1.55m.
This would be a 2.5 per cent fall from last year's already very depressed
level of 1.59m and would be a 33 per cent fall from the peak level of 2.3m
reached in 1989.
</TEXT>
