<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Milder winter helps Grafton advance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Grafton Group, the Dublin-based builders' merchant and DIY concern, lifted
pre-tax profits 14 per cent to IPounds 1.85m (Pounds 1.75m), in the six
months to June 30.
Mr Michael Chadwick, chairman, said the results reflected improved returns
from Irish operations and a reduced contribution from the smaller UK
operations. The milder winter helped the group during the half year.
Turnover improved to IPounds 48.7m (IPounds 45.7m) generating trading
profits of IPounds 2.55m (IPounds 2.17m). Interest charges rose to IPounds
698,000 (IPounds 553,000).
The interim dividend is stepped up to 2.75p (2.5p), payable from earnings of
8.6p (7.5p) per share.
For the full year, Mr Chadwick said the group was benefiting from the
investments and acquisitions made in 1991 and expected to record an increase
on the IPounds 3.55m pre-tax achieved last time.
</TEXT>
