FT  03 SEP 92 / Rail project granted Pounds 4.25m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RYAN MINING, the indep-endent coal producer, has received a Pounds 4.25m
grant from the Welsh Office to help it reopen the railway line in the Vale
of Neath and build a rail terminal at Cwmgwrach, West Glamorgan.
The terminal is part of a Pounds 14m project by the company to expand coal
mining in the Neath Valley area and dispense with road-borne coal haulage.
The project is expected to produce 600 jobs.
Ryan Mining, which specialises in underground mining, is part of Ryan Group
 -a possible purchaser of British Coal assets in the forthcoming
privatisation.
