FT  03 SEP 92 / Canada rules on partners' benefits
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ontario's Human Rights Commission has ruled that homosexuals are entitled to
their live-in partners' pension and insurance benefits in the same way as
spouses in a heterosexual marriage, writes Bernard Simon from Toronto.
The landmark ruling is expected to increase pressure on employers in Canada
to give equal access to spousal benefits for homosexuals, possibly leading
to increased costs for company-financed pension, insurance and health plans.
