<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 92 / UK Company News: ICI in Pounds 45m Diprivan expansion
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Imperial Chemical Industries is proceeding with a Pounds 45m expansion of
its production site near Milan. The move reflects the success of Diprivan,
its injectable anaesthetic.
The investment project at ICI-Pharma at Caponago will approximately double
capacity and increase flexibility in the manufacture of Diprivan. The
project, due for completion in late 1994, involves the purchase of 13,000 sq
m of land.
</TEXT>
