<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 92 / UK Company News: London Wall Pounds 1m down at nine months
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
London Wall Holdings, an underwriting agency at Lloyd's, suffered a fall in
profits from Pounds 1.45m to Pounds 445,000 pre-tax over the nine months to
June 30.
Turnover of Pounds 3.28m (Pounds 4.86m) was made up as to agency fees Pounds
2.59m (Pounds 2.64m), profit commission Pounds 615,000 (Pounds 2.16m), other
commission Pounds 25,000 (Pounds 24,000) and investment management fees
Pounds 44,000 (Pounds 32,000).
Earnings per share emerged at 6.51p (16.15p).
The shares are traded on the over-the-counter market.
</TEXT>
