FT  03 SEP 92 / UK Company News: TF &amp; JH Braime declines 25%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A 25 per cent fall in pre-tax profits, from Pounds 283,410 to Pounds
214,090, was announced by TF &amp; JH Braime (Holdings), the finished metal
products, forging, pressing and stamping group, for the half year to June
30.
Demand from UK customers remained at last year's depressed levels, the
company said. In such circumstances the performance of Braime Pressings, the
core business, had been 'satisfactory.'
However, overseas demand, particularly in the US and France, fell
substantially.
Turnover dropped to Pounds 2.78m (Pounds 3.51m). Investment income added
Pounds 75,677 (Pounds 59,165) but there were interest charges this time of
Pounds 17,408 (nil).
Earnings emerged at 9.65p (12.87p) and the interim dividend is maintained at
2.25p.
</TEXT>
