FT  03 SEP 92 / International Company News: Toshiba to form battery link
with Asahi
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVEN BUTLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TOSHIBA, the Japanese electronics company, and Asahi Chemical Industry, the
leading synthetic fibre maker, yesterday agreed to establish a joint venture
company to develop, manufacture and market rechargeable batteries for
portable electronic equipment, writes Steven Butler.
The companies are to manufacture lithium ion rechargeable batteries, which,
they claim, are light, small and environmentally friendly.
Power supply for electronic devices is becoming the bottleneck that limits
portability or use time for items such as notebook computers or cellular
telephones. The companies say lithium ion batteries provide twice the
capacity of nickel cadmium batteries.
The venture is to be called A&amp;T Battery. Sample shipment and marketing will
begin next month, while mass production will start in October next year with
a monthly production volume of 500,000 batteries.
Sales of Y30bn (Dollars 244m) are targeted for 1997.
