   By KEVIN BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CRA, the Australian mining group 49 per cent owned by RTZ of the UK,
yesterday said equity accounted net profit fell by 6.8 per cent to ADollars
128m (USDollars 91.4m) in the first half to the end of June, on turnover up
