Henry Schroder Wagg.
Mr David Barker, a director of Hoare Govett Corporate Finance, said the
issue was 'satisfactory despite the current volatility of the markets.'
Mr Barry Holder, general manager finance, said the issue 'allows us to write
more business at a time when the market is becoming more profitable '.
Commercial Union raised Pounds 100m via a preference issue in May.
