<TEXT>
NALGO, the local government union, yesterday failed in an effort to suspend
a High Court judge's order to call off a strike involving 1,100 staff at
Newham council in London, Lisa Wood writes.
The Court of Appeal refused the union's plea for a stay pending the hearing
of its appeal against a court order that the strike must end immediately.
The court rejected Nalgo's argument that the industrial action in response
to redundancies in the Labour council's poll-tax collection department
should be allowed to continue because calling it off now would make the
union's appeal pointless. The appeal is due to be heard next week.
