FT  03 SEP 92 / Receiverships on downward trend
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NUMBER of companies passing into receivership and administration has
declined for the seventh successive month compared with the corresponding
period a year before, according to figures released yesterday.
There were 327 appointments in August compared with 474 in July and 464 in
August last year, an analysis by accountants Touche Ross, based on the
official London and Edinburgh Gazettes, has revealed.
Mr Christopher Morris, head of corporate special services at Touche Ross,
said he remained 'cautiously optimistic' the downward trend would continue.
He stressed that the decline depended on lenders 'not losing their nerve'
about businesses' ability to survive.
The total number of appointments so far this year is 3,519 compared with
3,928 at the same time last year. Mr Morris estimated that with the current
trend there will be about 5,200 by the end of the year compared with 5,734
last year.
There remained many difficulties in the motor trade, hotel and catering, and
wholesale distribution, he explained. Manufacturing appointments declined to
79 for August, compared with an average monthly total of 120 in the year so
far.
</TEXT>
