<TEXT>
THE European Commission said yesterday it had ended an anti-dumping
investigation regarding wire rods sold in the EC and made in Argentina,
Egypt, Turkey, Trinidad and Tobago and the Yugoslav republics, AP reports
from Brussels.
The Commission said in a statement that it has closed the inquiry following
a decision by the European Confederation of Iron and Steel Industries
